k is chairman of bda china a consultancy he founded in beijing in 1994 after four years as an investment banker with morgan stanley in london and hong kong over the past 18 years duncan has guided bda to become the leading investment advisory firm in china specialized in china's technology internet and ecommerce sectors duncan is also a senior advisor to the china 2.0 initiative at sprie where he was invited as a visiting scholar from 2010 2011 a partner at mobile game app developer happy latte he has also served on the advisory board of netease com nasdaq ntes and serves on the advisory board of the digital communication fund of geneva based bank pictet & cie a uk citizen duncan was raised in england the united states and france he is the elected chairman of the british chamber of commerce in china vice chair of the china britain business council and vice chair of the ict working group of the european chamber of commerce in china downloads audio audio podcast of the sprie seminar on the creation of the venture capital pe backed entrepreneurial community in china with howard chao and duncn clark streaming mp3 pdf+ white paper onshore financial investing in china modified february 2012 pdf white_paper_on_onshore_investm pdf 183.7 kb pdf+ vie structures in china what you need to know modified february 2012 pdf ticl_ _vie_structures_in_china pdf 625.5 kb location g101 dunlevie classroom 1st floor gunn building knight management center stanford graduate school of business 655 knight way stanford ca94305 7298 fsi contact yan mei topics business entrepreneurship investment venture capital china search sprie events of interest the evolution of venture capital in japan a case study michael korver audio+ pdf+ the development of the venture capital industry in singapore poh kam wong support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds stanford program on regions of innovation and entrepreneurship stanford graduate school of business knight management center mcclelland bldg 655